DocConstant.Name: RESIDUALCURRENTCIRCUITBREAKER
DocConstant.Documentation: A device that opens, closes, or isolates a circuit and has short circuit and overload protection. It attempts to break the circuit when there is a difference in current between any two phases. May also be referred to as 'Ground Fault Interupter (GFI)' or 'Ground Fault Circuit Interuptor (GFCI)'
